    <item>
      <title>Emoji Not Showing Properly on Archlinux.md</title>
      <link>https://greasycat.github.io/posts/tools/emoji-not-showing-properly-on-archlinux.md/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 02 Jun 2022 19:26:39 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://greasycat.github.io/posts/tools/emoji-not-showing-properly-on-archlinux.md/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The issue persisted for a long time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emojis in kconsole are displayed as blocks(cubes) even though the noto-font-emoji had been installed. Luckily I found a solution today&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://flammie.github.io/dotfiles/fontconfig.html&#34;&gt;Original Solution&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basically, I inserted the following lines to &lt;code&gt;/etc/font/fonts.conf&lt;/code&gt; inside the &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;font-config&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; tag&lt;/p&gt;
